{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox film | name = Ice and the Sky | image = Ice and the Sky.jpg | caption = Film poster | director = [[Luc Jacquet]] | producer = Richard Grandpierre | writer = Luc Jacquet | starring = [[Claude Lorius]] | music = Cyrille Aufort | cinematography = Stéphane Martin | editing = Stéphane Mazalaigue | distributor = [[Pathé Distribution]] | released = {{Film date|2015|5|24|[[2015 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]|2015|10|21|France|df=yes}} | runtime = | country = France | language = French | budget = }}
'''''Ice and the Sky''''' ({{lang-fr|'''La Glace et le ciel'''}}, also known as '''''Antarctica: Ice and Sky''''') is a 2015 French [[documentary film]] directed by [[Luc Jacquet]] about the work of [[Claude Lorius]], who began studying Antarctic ice in 1957, and, in 1965, was the first scientist to be concerned about global warming.<ref name="Variety">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/reviews/film-review-ice-and-the-sky-1201509215/ |title=Film Review: ‘Ice and the Sky’ |date=13 December 2016 |accessdate=13 December 2016 |work=Variety}}</ref> The film was selected to close the [[2015 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name="closing">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/article/61330.html |title=A hymn to save the planet as the Closing Film of the Cannes Film Festival: Ice and the Sky by Luc Jacquet |date=30 April 2015 |accessdate=30 April 2015 |work=Cannes Film Festival}}</ref>
