'''Ikeja Electric''' Plc is the largest [[Nigeria]]n power distribution company. It is based in [[Ikeja]], capital of the state of [[Lagos (state)|Lagos]].  The company emerged on November 1, 2013 following the handover of the defunct [[Power Holding Company of Nigeria]] (PHCN) to NEDC/[[Korea Electric Power Corporation|KEPCO]] Consortium under the privatization scheme of the [[Federal Government of Nigeria]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nigeriaelectricityhub.com/tag/nigerias-largest-power-distribution-network/|title=Nigeria’s largest power distribution network {{!}} Nigeria Electricity|website=www.nigeriaelectricityhub.com|access-date=2016-09-20}}</ref>

==Operations==
Ikeja Electric has over 700,000 customers. Ikeja Electric's introduced a Debt Discount initiative which provides various percentage discount options to enable customers pay off their outstanding bills and meet their financial obligations to the company. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.informationng.com/2016/06/compensation-and-benefits-supervisor-at-ikeja-electricity-distribution-company-ikedc.html|title=Compensation and Benefits Supervisor at Ikeja Electricity Distribution Company (IKEDC) - INFORMATION NIGERIA|access-date=2016-09-20}}</ref>

