{{Infobox power station | name = Karlshamn Power Station | name_official = Karlshamnsverket | image = Karlshamnsverket.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Sweden | location_map_size = | location_map_caption= | coordinates = {{coord|56|9|8|N|14|49|57|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = [[Sweden]] | location = [[Karlshamn]] | status = Operational | construction_began = | commissioned = 1969 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[E.ON Sverige]] | operator = Karlshamn Kraft | th_fuel_primary = [[Fuel oil]] | th_fuel_tertiary = | ps_units_operational= 3 x 335&nbsp;MW | ps_units_manu_model = | th_cogeneration = | th_combined_cycle = | ps_electrical_capacity= 1,000 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac= | website = [http://www.karlshamnkraft.se/CM.php?PageID=65094 www.karlshamnkraft.se] | extra = }}
'''Karlshamn Power Station''' (also known as '''Stärnö Power Station''', {{lang-sv|Karlshamnsverket}}) is an oil-fired [[thermal power station]] on Stärnö peninsula west of [[Karlshamn]]. It has three units each with a generation capacity of 340&nbsp;MW, which went in service in 1969, 1971 and 1973. Each unit has its own {{convert|141|m}} tall [[flue gas stack]]. Unit 1 delivers its power to the 130&nbsp;kV grid, while unit 2 and 3 feed the 400&nbsp;kV grid. Next to the power station, a converter station of the [[SwePol|SwePol HVDC submarine cable]] is located.
== External links == {{Portal|Sweden|Energy}} * http://www.karlshamnkraft.se/CM.php?PageID=61455
[[Category:Oil-fired power stations in Sweden]]
