{{Infobox Protected area | name = Mulayit Wildlife Sanctuary | iucn_category = IV | photo = | photo_caption = | map = Burma | relief = 1 | map_alt = | map_caption = Location within Burma | map_width = | location =[[Kayin State]], [[Burma]] | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coord|16|18|N|98|31|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | area = {{convert|139|km2|sqmi|sigfig=3}} | established = 1936 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }}
'''Mulayit Wildlife Sanctuary''' is a small [[protected area]] in [[Kayin State]], [[Burma]]. It is located around [[Mulayit Taung|Mulayit]] mountain in the [[Dawna Range]].
The reserve occupies an area of {{convert|139|km2|sqmi|sigfig=3}}<ref>[http://www.mekonginfo.org/assets/midocs/0002035-environment-biodiversity-and-protected-areas-myanmar.pdf Biodiversity and protected areas - Myanmar]</ref> and was established in 1936.<ref>[http://www.protectedplanet.net/sites/Mulayit_Wildlife_Sanctuary Protected Planet - Mulayit Wildlife Sanctuary]</ref>
==Flora and fauna== The [[white-fronted scops owl]],<ref>[http://birdbase.hokkaido-ies.go.jp/rdb/rdb_en/otussagi.pdf Birdbase]</ref> the [[silver-eared laughingthrush]] (''Trochalopteron melanostigma''),<ref>[http://worldbirdinfo.net/Pages/BirdCitationView.aspx?BirdID=38180&Source=%2FPages%2FBirdsSearch.aspx%3FBirdField%3D6%26BirdSearch%3DTIMALIIDAE%253ABabblers World Bird Info]</ref> the [[grey-sided thrush]] (''Turdus feae''), a [[vulnerable species]],<ref>[http://www.birdlife.org/datazone/userfiles/file/Species/AsRDBPDFs/species/turdfeae.pdf Threatened Birds of Asia: The BirdLife International Red Data Book]</ref> and the [[Tenasserim white-bellied rat]] (''Niviventer tenaster'')<ref>Mammal species of the world:a taxonomic and geographic reference, Volume 2</ref> are found in the Mulayit Taung area.
The wildlife sanctuary is an [[insurgency]] area and wildlife biodiversity is declining. Protection of species is compromised for all the forests of the region have seen unprecedented destruction in recent years.<ref>[http://bijstbnd.home.xs4all.nl/birma/birma-24.html Mu Traw district - Status of the Rainforest]</ref>
