'''Oatmeal paper''' is a [[paper]] made from [[oatmeal]]. In [[Korea]], Oatmeal paper is called as '''Hwangji''' (황지, 黃紙, Yellow paper). [[Jaegaseung]] ([[Jurchen people]] descendants who live in Korea) produced this paper and substitute their tax to oatmeal paper.<ref>[http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1936010100209251001&edtNo=1&printCount=1&publishDate=1936-01-01&officeId=00020&pageNo=51&printNo=5421&publishType=00020 Dong-A ilbo], January 1, 1936, 56th page</ref>

